{
  "texts": [
    "Given any two observables O A, O B on the n-qubit system, we define the distance d obs (O A, O B) between the two observables as the minimum distance between the qubits that O A and O B act on.",
    "We also say an observable is geometrically local if it acts nontrivially only on nearby qubits under the distance metric d qubit.",
    "We then define S (geo) as the set of all geometrically local Pauli observables, i.e., geometrically local observables that belong to the set {I, X, Y, Z} ⊗n.",
    "The size of S (geo) is OðnÞ, linear in the total number of qubits.",
    "With these basic definitions in place, we now define a few more geometric objects."
  ]
}